2a^2+4b^2+c^2=4ab+2ac
cos B
a,b,c
A,B,C
7/8
2a^2+4b^2+c^2=4ab+2ac\iff (a-2b)^2+(a-c)^2=0
a=c=2b
 \cos B=\frac{a^2+c^2-b^2}{2ac}=\frac{4b^2+4b^2-b^2}{8b^2}=\frac{7}{8}. 
a^2+c^2\geq 2ac
a^2+4b^2\geq 4ab
 a=c \quad \text{and} \quad a=2b. 
 \cos B=\frac{a^2+c^2-b^2}{2ac}=\frac{4b^2+4b^2-b^2}{8b^2}=\frac{7}{8}. 
